<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,338,1084]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,538,564]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Description</emphasis>
. Colonies generally small (less than 
<quantity box="[799,861,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
high), delicate, composed of single pedicellate hydranths or erect and few branched stems, arising from a creeping stolon. Perisarc thin and transparent or slightly brown basally, annulated at base of side branches (2–7 annuli), smooth elsewhere. Hydranths urnshaped, with 14–20 filiform tentacles. Gonophores not seen. Cnidome:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,338,1084]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">a) small microbasic euryteles on tentacles, undischarged (6.9–7.2) x (3.3–3.6) µm, discharged (6.9–7.2) x (3.6–3.9) µm;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,338,1084]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">b) large macrobasic euryteles on hydranth body, hypostome, fewer in the coenosarc, undischarged (21.0– 22.3) x (10.2–10.8) µm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,338,1084]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,858,884]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. The identification of this hydroid is somewhat uncertain because gonophores are lacking. Neverthless, the present material agrees well with the description and illustrations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puce, Cerrano &amp; Bavestrello" authorityYear="2002" box="[1092,1187,898,923]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eudendriidae" genus="Eudendrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="scotti">
<emphasis box="[1092,1187,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">E. scotti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Puce, S. &amp; Cerrano, C. &amp; Bavestrello, G." box="[1230,1436,898,924]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="366 - 373" refId="ref80694" refString="Puce, S., Cerrano, C. &amp; Bavestrello, G. (2002) Eudendrium (Cnidaria, Anthomedusae) from the Antarctic Ocean, with description of two new species. Polar Biology, 25, 366 - 373." type="journal article" year="2002">
Puce 
<emphasis box="[1293,1344,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al</emphasis>
. (2002)
</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[215,340,938,964]" name="Antarctica" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
, who also described the gonophores of this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,338,1084]" box="[199,1070,978,1004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,434,978,1004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">World distribution</emphasis>
. Reported only from the Antarctic (
<bibRefCitation author="Puce, S. &amp; Cerrano, C. &amp; Bavestrello, G." box="[854,1057,978,1004]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="366 - 373" refId="ref80694" refString="Puce, S., Cerrano, C. &amp; Bavestrello, G. (2002) Eudendrium (Cnidaria, Anthomedusae) from the Antarctic Ocean, with description of two new species. Polar Biology, 25, 366 - 373." type="journal article" year="2002">
Puce 
<emphasis box="[921,979,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
, 2002
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
